HEADWORD: Lalo
<hw>La"lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The powdered leaves of
the baobab tree, used by the Africans to mix in their soup, as the
southern negroes use powdered sassafras. Cf.
<er>Couscous</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

